article.description: James Madison holds on to beat Elon 75-72
article.headline: James Madison holds on to beat Elon 75-72
article.linkText: James Madison holds on to beat Elon 75-72
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Jackson Kent scored 15 points and forced a late turnover to help James Madison hold off and beat Elon 75-72 on Saturday night. Elon overcame an 11-point second half deficit and pulled within 71-70 with 1:13 remaining. James Madison's Yohanny Dalembert scored, Kent had a steal, and Ron Curry hit a jumper to stretch the lead the Dukes' lead to 75-70 with 27 seconds left. Austin Hamilton answered for Elon, making it 75-72. While anticipating an intentional foul, Kent turned the ball over to Dmitri Thompson to give Elon a final opportunity with 7 seconds left. But Hamilton's potential game-tying 3 was long to seal it for James Madison (11-8, 4-2 Colonial Athletic Association). Dalembert had 16 points and Curry finished with 10. Tanner Samson scored 18 points to lead Elon (10-9, 2-4). Hamilton had 11 and Kevin Blake chipped in 10 for the Phoenix.
